# Seven-languages

Homework for "Seven languages in seven weeks" book. So this is the erlang week ...

## Usage

If you use homebrew, you know what to do:

    brew install erlang

Otherwise, check somewhere [here](http://www.erlang.org/download.html).

Very short cheat sheet with `erl`:

  * compile a module: `c(module).`
  * launch tests: `module:test().` More [here](http://www.erlang.org/doc/apps/eunit/chapter.html)
  * exit: `halt().`

More [here](http://www.erlang.org/documentation/doc-5.3/doc/getting_started/getting_started.html)

